                <p>Raskolnikov was sitting on the river bank, looking at the wide, deserted river. From the high bank a broad landscape was visible. From the other bank far away came the faint sound of singing. There, in the boundless steppe, flooded with sunlight, the black tents of the nomads were dotted like specks. There was freedom there, there other people were living, utterly unlike those here; there time itself seemed to stand still, as though the age of Abraham and his flocks had not passed.</p>
